The paper deals with few-shot classification, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of metric-based methods and feature embeddings further suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision sub-category of cs.CV. The paper also involves the use of learning-to-learn approaches, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.LG. Additionally, the paper involves the use of domain generalization, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as data augmentation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL. Finally, the paper involves the use of image datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM, which deals with multimedia.
